                            <comment id="12762800" author="henryr" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 23:01:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch ups the limit of concurrently active connections to 32768, and allocates these handles dynamically in increasing powers of two.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Handles are re-used when they are correctly closed. This involves an O&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/thumbs_down.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; scan of the handle array, but I think this is preferable to the overhead of managing linked lists with O(1) lookup. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests are included.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
